text:
Livingston Place, east side, north from, and including East 16th to 17th Streets, showing the Beth Israel Hospital, as seen looking across Stuyvesant Square Park.

1923.

P. L. Sperr.

Livingston Place, north from East 16th to 17th Street's, showing the northeasterly corner of Stuyvesant Park. The buildings in the background are on the north side of East 17th Street, east of Second Avenue. This thoroughfare is at the extreme left and is not shown. At the right is the Beth Israel Hospital.

July 19, 1939

P. L. Sperr
